<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERTUSSIS REACTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: If a child has had a bad reaction to the pertussis vaccine, should he 
not get any more shots? Or is it better to take the chance that the bad 
reaction won't happen again? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: For children who have had a bad reaction to the 
diphtheria-tetanus-pertussis (DTP) vaccine, a vaccine is available that does 
not contain the pertussis portion. 
</P>
<P>
Q: I can understand why aerobic exercises are supposed to be good for the heart 
and the lungs. What do all these people who do anaerobic exercises get out of 
them? 
</P>
<P>
A: The main purpose of anaerobic exercise is to increase muscle strength. The 
greatest benefits to overall health come from aerobic exercise. 
</P>
<P>
For Mrs. D.S., Montpelier, Vt.: Women who have reduced iron reserves have less 
energy and will tire faster during exercise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
