<HEADLINE>
<P>
COOK IT LIGHT: REDUCING FAT IN 'DELICIOUS' BREAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNE JONES, Jones is a food consultant and a cookbook author. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DEAR JEANNE: This recipe looks delicious, but I want to try to decrease the 
fat. 
</P>
<P>
 -- MARY, Fort Worth, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
DOM DELUISE'S CHEESE AND ONION BREAD 
</P>
<P>
1 1/2 cups chopped onions 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons butter 
</P>
<P>
1 egg 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup sour cream 
</P>
<P>
Pepper 
</P>
<P>
2 cups flour 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon baking powder 
</P>
<P>
1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese 
</P>
<P>
2/3 cup milk 
</P>
<P>
3 tablespoons minced fresh parsley 
</P>
<P>
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Combine onions with egg, 
sour cream and pepper to taste in bowl, mixing well. Set aside. 
</P>
<P>
Place flour and baking powder in another bowl. Cut in remaining 1/4 cup butter 
until crumbly and fine. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese. Add milk to make soft dough. 
</P>
<P>
Pat into buttered 9-inch square pan. Spread sour cream mixture on top. Sprinkle 
with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and parsley. Bake at 425 degrees 25 minutes. Cut 
into squares and serve warm. Makes 8 servings. 
</P>
<P>
DEAR MARY: In spite of the changes I have made and the huge reduction in 
calories, cholesterol, fat and sodium, most people would not be able to tell 
the difference between the original and my revision. I took advantage of the 
reduced-fat products now in the markets to lower the calories and fat from the 
sour cream and the cheese. Using egg whites instead of a whole egg eliminates 
the cholesterol from the yolk, and nonfat milk instead of whole milk also 
worked beautifully. 
</P>
<P>
 -- JEANNE 
</P>
<P>
JEANNE'S CHEESE AND ONION BREAD 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon corn-oil margarine 
</P>
<P>
1 1/2 cups chopped onions 
</P>
<P>
2 egg whites 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup light sour cream 
</P>
<P>
1/8 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper 
</P>
<P>
2 cups unbleached flour 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon baking powder 
</P>
<P>
1 cup shredded 20% fat-reduced Cheddar cheese 
</P>
<P>
2/3 cup nonfat milk 
</P>
<P>
3 tablespoons minced fresh parsley 
</P>
<P>
Melt 1 teaspoon margarine in skillet over medium heat. Saute onions until soft, 
then cool slightly. Add egg whites, sour cream and pepper. Mix well and set 
aside. 
</P>
<P>
Combine flour and baking powder in mixing bowl. Cut in remaining 2 tablespoons 
margarine with pastry blender or fork until crumbly and fine. Stir in 1/2 cup 
shredded cheese. Add milk and stir to make soft dough. 
</P>
<P>
Pat dough into 9-inch square pan sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating. 
Spread sour cream mixture on top. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and 
parsley. Bake at 425 degrees 25 minutes. Cut into squares and serve 
immediately. Makes 8 servings. 
</P>
<P>
Each serving contains approximately: 
</P>
<P>
Original Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
375 calories 
</P>
<P>
92 mg cholesterol 
</P>
<P>
24 gm fat 
</P>
<P>
561 mg sodium 
</P>
<P>
Revised Recipe: 
</P>
<P>
200 calories 
</P>
<P>
18 mg cholesterol 
</P>
<P>
6 gm fat 
</P>
<P>
338 mg sodium 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
