<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DIAMOND BAR; 
</P>
<P>
1-YEAR CELEBRATION BEGINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city has decided to throw itself a party to celebrate its first year of 
incorporation. Officials are planning an all-day picnic April 21 at Carlton J. 
Peterson Park. 
</P>
<P>
The event, proposed by City Council members John Forbing and Gary Werner, will 
include a softball tournament, food bazaar, citizen recognition awards, 
children's games, races and relays and a tree-planting ceremony. The City 
Council on Tuesday night appointed a committee to plan the activities, but 
members said they expect the project to be a communitywide effort. 
</P>
<P>
Diamond Bar, which has 45,000 residents and encompasses 8,000 acres of rolling 
hills, is the 86th city to be incorporated in Los Angeles County. It is one of 
the fastest-growing communities in the San Gabriel Valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
