</P>
<P>
FOUNDATION PICKS LA VERNE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The University of La Verne has been selected to participate in the 
Sears-Roebuck Foundation's 1989-90 "Teaching Excellence and Campus Leadership 
Award Program." 
</P>
<P>
The Sears-Roebuck awards are distributed among more than 700 of the nation's 
leading private liberal arts colleges and universities and recognize top 
educators on each campus for their resourcefulness and leadership. 
</P>
<P>
Winners will be selected by a group of administrators, faculty and alumni. 
</P>
<P>
Each winning faculty member will receive $1,000 and the University of La Verne 
will get an institutional grant of $1,500 to encourage faculty enrichment, 
campus leadership and improved teaching. 
</P>
