<P>
CAL POLY ADDS PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal Poly Pomona has launched an off-campus degree program in business 
administration. 
</P>
<P>
Classes will be held at the General Dynamics Valley Systems Division in Pomona. 
They will be taught by instructors from Cal Poly's College of Business 
Administration. The degree program is a cooperative effort between the 
university and General Dynamics. 
</P>
<P>
The General Dynamics program is one of several outreach programs being offered 
in the Pomona Valley. This month, Cal Poly Pomona's Office of Continuing 
Education will open an off-campus site at the Ontario Public Library, where 
credit and non-credit courses will be offered. 
</P>
<P>
Classes taught at the new location will include landscape technology, 
management and human resources and teacher education. 
