<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAYLE TO ATTEND LATIN INAUGURAL AND VISIT EUROPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vice President Dan Quayle will attend the Jan. 27 inauguration of the new 
president of Honduras and will visit Europe next month, his spokesman said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Quayle's schedule includes a one-day visit to Honduras for the inauguration of 
Rafael Leonardo Callejas, elected in November, said Quayle's press secretary, 
David Beckwith. 
</P>
<P>
Sources said the possibility of additional stops in the region -- such as 
Panama or El Salvador -- are under consideration. 
</P>
<P>
The vice president will be in Europe from Feb. 4-11, with stops planned at 
North Atlantic Treaty Organization headquarters in Brussels, Geneva, London and 
Bonn and Munich, West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Quayle may also visit Berlin and Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
<P>
"He wants to consult with our allies on U.S.-European issues of the '90s," 
Beckwith said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
