<TEXT>
<P>
CBS Lawsuit Settlement OKd: A federal judge approved a $6-million settlement of 
a suit filed by a CBS shareholder who claimed the firm that owns the CBS 
television network was mismanaged from 1983 to 1986. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit was brought in 1986 by Roger Minkoff, a real estate investor from 
St. Croix, Virgin Islands, who owns 12 CBS shares. The settlement, in which CBS 
Inc. management admits no wrongdoing, will be paid by a corporate insurance 
policy. It was reached Nov. 28. Of the settlement, $4.5 million will go to the 
CBS treasury for an indirect benefit to shareholders. The remaining $1.5 
million will go to Minkoff's attorney. Minkoff will receive $15,000 from the 
attorney's portion. 
</P>
