<HEADLINE>
<P>
MERRILL LYNCH TO SELL CANADIAN SECURITIES UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TORONTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Merrill Lynch &amp; Co., which has been trying to cut costs in a bid to boost 
flagging profits, said Wednesday that it has agreed to sell its entire Canadian 
retail securities business to Canadian brokerage Wood Gundy Inc. for 
undisclosed terms. 
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch, the No. 1 U.S. securities firm, said the deal includes the 
transfer of its Canadian offices and work force as well as access to its U.S. 
research facilities. 
</P>
<P>
Wood Gundy Chairman G. Edmund King told a press conference that the deal was 
attractive because of Merrill Lynch's "broad distribution, superior client 
service and new products." 
</P>
<P>
Merrill Lynch's retail sales force in Canada includes 264 registered 
representatives and 156 managerial and sales support personnel, as well as 265 
operations and systems employees in 20 Canadian offices. 
</P>
<P>
Wood Gundy, one of Canada's largest brokerages, has 385 registered 
representatives operating in 39 offices across Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
