<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANADIAN CLIMBER DIES ON COLOMBIA PEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canadian mountain climber Pascall Vieau, missing for a week, was found dead on 
the Nevado del Tolima mountain by the Colombian Red Cross, authorities said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Vieau, 22, died when he fell off the icy slope into an abyss, press reports 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Vieau had begun the climb with four Colombian mountaineers, but on Dec. 27 he 
decided to continue alone to the peak, a Red Cross spokesman said. The 
Canadian's body was found Tuesday, 12,210 feet above sea level at La Cueva, on 
the 17,210-foot-high, snowcapped mountain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
