<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
SHOOTING VICTIM IN STABLE CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES ROBBINS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Anaheim man was wounded by gunfire outside El Tropico Bar at 900 S. Anaheim 
Blvd. around 6 p.m. Tuesday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Efrain Tejada-Barron was in the intensive care unit at Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana on Wednesday, listed in stable condition, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim police were called to an apartment complex at 944 S. Anaheim Blvd. at 
6:05 Tuesday, where they found Tejada-Barron. A bullet had entered his hip and 
exited through his abdomen, Anaheim Police Lt. Marc Hedgpeth said. 
</P>
<P>
Hedgpeth said Tejada-Barron had reportedly argued with a young man at El 
Tropico. The two men stepped outside to fight and the young man pulled a weapon 
and shot Tejada-Barron. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman fled and could not be found, and Tejada-Barron "fled or stumbled" to 
the front of the apartment complex where he was found, Hedgpeth said. 
Tejada-Barron refused to give his address to police and didn't identify a 
possible suspect, he said. JAMES ROBBINS 
</P>
</TEXT>
