<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
GROUP OFFERS GUIDED TOURS OF WETLANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free walking tours of the Bolsa Chica wetlands will be offered Saturday morning 
by the environmental organization Amigos de Bolsa Chica. 
</P>
<P>
Those wishing to take the tours should come to the Bolsa Chica Ecological 
Reserve parking lot off Pacific Coast Highway across from Bolsa Chica State 
Beach. Tours will begin every 20 minutes from 9 a.m. to 10:30 a.m., starting 
from the parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
Participants are advised to wear warm clothing and sturdy shoes and to bring 
binoculars. 
</P>
<P>
The wetlands have large populations of ducks, terns and a small colony of white 
pelicans. 
</P>
<P>
More information about the tours and about the training program for docents may 
be obtained from the Amigos de Bolsa Chica office at (714) 897-7003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
