<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CONLISK, LOS ALAMITOS HOLD OFF WESTERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robert Conlisk scored 24 points and had 12 rebounds to lead Los Alamitos High 
School to a 66-64 victory over Western Wednesday in a boys' nonleague 
basketball game at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos led by five points with about two minutes to play, but Western 
rallied. The Pioneers cut their deficit to 66-64 in the final 20 seconds, but 
never touched the ball again. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Cunningham had 12 points and six assists for Los Alamitos. Sam Sabbara 
scored 14 for Western. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Jordan 61, Marina 39 -- Marina led, 31-30, after three quarters but 
was outscored in the final quarter, 31-8. Cherokee Parks led Marina with 19 
points. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 72, Trabuco Hills 63 -- Dave Beilstein and Phuong Tran had 20 points 
each for host Tustin (12-2). Bo Hossler had 21 for Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Millikan 67, Huntington Beach 53 -- Mustapha Abdi had 17 points and 15 rebounds 
for Huntington Beach (7-7). James Maddred led all scorers with 20 points for 
Millikan. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei 73, Palisades 49 -- Reserve David Boyle ignited a third-quarter rally 
by scoring 11 of his game-high 26 points as Mater Dei (13-1) overcame a 
lethargic first-half performance. Boyle scored 26 points in 21 minutes and 
snapped a three-week shooting slump by making 11 of 16 shots. 
</P>
<P>
Servite 60, Burroughs 47 -- Mike Coady had 17 points and Steve Marusich 16 to 
lead host Servite (8-6). 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 71, Anaheim 50 -- Abdi Barkhordar had 23 points and Kevin Wilborn 15 to 
lead Canyon (7-7). Danny Castro had 18 points for Anaheim, which had three 
technical fouls. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 72, Westminster 69 -- Jason Perrotto scored 22 points for visiting 
Cypress (7-7). Jessie Gomez and Eden Yawata had 16 each for Westminster (6-7). 
</P>
<P>
Sonora 62, Orange 55 -- Roy Park and Scott Oxarart each had 12 points to lead 
host Sonora (5-8). Greg Farlow added 11 for Sonora, which outscored Orange, 
28-13, in the second half. Orange's Carlos Duran had a game-high 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
El Modena 56, Magnolia 45 -- Jeff Leedom had 16 points and Gregg Gottlieb 15 to 
lead host El Modena (8-6). Wayne Thomas had 16 points for Magnolia (2-8). 
</P>
<P>
St. Margaret's 76, Midway 49 -- Ryan Westendorf scored 28 points and had 18 
rebounds and Dann Campaine added 22 points and 17 rebounds for visiting St. 
Margaret's (6-4). 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 63, Foothill 55 -- Paig Parish scored 20 points and Eddie 
Martinez 19 for visiting Newport Harbor. The Sailors led after three quarters, 
47-46, and outscored Foothill, 16-9, in the final quarter. Mark Wilkinson 
scored 25 and Fred Amos 13 for Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
University 87, Santa Ana Valley 74 -- University (5-7) made 27 of 40 free 
throws as Santa Ana Valley (3-7) was called for 51 personal fouls. Klaus Perwas 
scored 31 points for University. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado 86, Sunny Hills 57 -- Guard Mike Bradach scored 29 points as visiting 
El Dorado handed Sunny Hills its 10th loss in 12 games. Dominic Carnesi had 24 
points for Sunny Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia 60, Costa Mesa 41 -- Guard Augustin Heredia scored 12 of his game-high 
20 points in the first quarter when Estancia (9-4) opened a 20-8 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills 62, La Habra 31 -- J.B. Taylor scored 16 as Dana Hills (12-3) won at 
home. James Klegg, one of La Habra's top players, was ill and didn't play. Mark 
Moreno scored 13 for La Habra. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo 71, Woodbridge 58 -- Eric Cramer scored 19 and Mark Wright 16 for 
host Mission Viejo (9-4). 
</P>
<P>
In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 89, Kennedy 72 -- David Green had 25 points and eight assists 
to lead Rancho Alamitos (7-3, 1-0). Paul Preuss had 17 points for Rancho 
Alamitos. Rod Rosales had 12 points for Kennedy (3-6, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 62, La Quinta 58 -- Randy Schulze scored 15 points and Tim Wahen 14 
for visiting Pacifica (3-6, 1-0). Dusty DePree scored 19 and Walter Dawkins had 
10 points and seven assists for La Quinta (0-9, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande 61, Los Amigos 58 -- Eddie Benson had 16 points in a losing cause 
for Los Amigos. 
</P>
