<TEXT>
<P>
A bodyguard to Manuel Antonio Noriega overheard two U.S. servicemen discussing 
the invasion of Panama hours before it occurred, a Pentagon spokesman said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
It was unclear, however, whether the guard relayed that information to Noriega 
or whether the incident played any role in the U.S. failure to capture Noriega 
in the days after the invasion. 
</P>
