that this operation was about to happen. But there isn't a lot of evidence that 
actions were taken as a result of that," Defense Department spokesman Pete 
Williams told reporters. 
</P>
<P>
"A bodyguard during a debriefing interview said that two U.S. soldiers had been 
overheard discussing their positions for H-hour. And that supposedly happened 
at 10 p.m., three hours before the attack was to begin," Williams said. 
