<TEXT>
<P>
Apple Computer Inc. said today its board of directors has approved the 
repurchase of up to 2.5 million additional shares of common stock. 
</P>
<P>
The ongoing open-market purchases are part of a program announced last August 
when Apple's board first authorized the purchase of 2.5 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
John Sculley, Apple's chairman and chief executive, said the purchase 
"represents good long-term value to our shareholders." 
</P>
<P>
Last month, Apple projected a decline in earnings in the first quarter of 
fiscal 1990 and said sales will grow more slowly than previously predicted. 
</P>
<P>
That announcement surprised industry watchers, coming just two weeks after a 
top executive of the personal computer maker told security analysts in New York 
that it expected worldwide sales growth of more than 20%. 
