<P>
PRODUCER SUES 'BORN' AUTHOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A producer is suing Ron Kovic, the Vietnam veteran whose autobiography was made 
into the film "Born on the Fourth of July," contending that the author sold him 
the movie rights and then failed to help make the film. 
</P>
<P>
Mel Goldberg, in a lawsuit filed Wednesday in Superior Court in Los Angeles, 
alleges that Kovic sold him the film rights to the book in 1985 and agreed to 
put Goldberg in touch with such Hollywood figures as actors and potential 
financiers. 
</P>
<P>
Goldberg contends that Kovic breached the contract by never setting up meetings 
and failing to allow renewal of the movie option. He is seeking $1 million in 
general damages and unspecified punitive damages. 
</P>
<P>
Telephone calls to Kovic were not immediately returned. 
</P>
<P>
"Born on the Fourth of July," starring Tom Cruise as the young soldier who 
returns from Vietnam as a paraplegic, was released last month by Universal 
Pictures. 
</P>
