<P>
N.Z. YACHT HOLDS NARROW LEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
AUCKLAND, New Zealand 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Zealand yacht Steinlager II held a narrow lead tonight as the leading 
yachts in the third leg of the Whitbread round-the-world ocean race neared 
Auckland. 
</P>
<P>
Steinlager II, winner of the first two legs of the 33,000-nautical-mile race, 
held a lead of two nautical miles over New Zealand rival Fisher and Paykel, 
skippered by Grant Dalton, as the leaders rounded Cape Reinga, 180 nautical 
miles from Auckland. 
</P>
<P>
Race officials said the leaders could reach Auckland as early as Friday 
afternoon after sailing 3,434 nautical miles from Fremantle in Western 
Australia. 
</P>
<P>
Six miles behind Fisher and Paykel in third place was the British sloop 
Rothmans, skippered by Lawrie Smith. 
</P>
