<P>
LAYCOCK INTERVIEWED BY NAVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANNAPOLIS, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William &amp; Mary football Coach Jimmye Laycock has interviewed for the 
coaching job at Navy, according to a published report today. 
</P>
<P>
Laycock, who coached William &amp; Mary to an 8-3-1 record in 1989, was the 
second to interview for the post. 
</P>
<P>
Sources told the Baltimore Sun that Laycock met with the athletic board 
Wednesday. Laycock interviewed for the Navy job the last time it was open, 
after Gary Tranquill was not offered a new contract after the 1986 season. 
</P>
<P>
Laycock is the second candidate known to have been invited to the academy to 
meet with board members. Former Detroit Lions Coach Darryl Rogers interviewed 
last week. 
</P>
<P>
Navy fired Elliot Uzelac last month and has set a Jan. 12 deadline for hiring a 
new coach. 
</P>
<P>
Other candidates are Virginia assistant Coach Tim O'Brien and Gene Stallings, 
former Phoenix Cardinals coach. 
</P>
